  "prompt": "Are maps of New York City free?",
  "response": "Free maps of New York City can be obtained from various sources. Here are some options:\n\n1. **Tourist Information Centers**: You can find free NYC maps at tourist information centers, such as the one located in Midtown Manhattan.\n\n2. **Hotels**: Many hotels in NYC offer free maps to their guests at the front desk or concierge.\n\n3. **Public Libraries**: The New York Public Library and other local libraries often have free maps available.\n\n4. **Online Resources**: Websites like Google Maps, OpenStreetMap, and the official NYC website offer free digital maps that you can download or print.\n\n5. **Transportation Hubs**: Places like Penn Station, Grand Central Terminal, and major subway stations often have free maps available.\n\n6. **Visitor Centers**: Centers like the one at One World Trade Center may provide free maps to visitors.\n\nWhile physical maps are often free at these locations, some specialty or detailed maps might require purchase. Always a good idea to call ahead or check online to confirm availability.",
